about: I am a 36 year old sociable Dutch guy, working in publishing in Amsterdam.

review.comments:
Great location with Tram & Metro just a few meters away and only 10min travel time or less to any main location/attraction in Amsterdam.  

Felt good to be able to come in and out of the busy streets and catch brakes at any time we felt we needed it.  if you there for more than 2 nights and decide not to rent a bike, definitely buy a 24hr or more travel ticket which is valid in trams and trains for sure... maybe even buses but we didn't need that. 

Apartment is great, clean and simple. Lounge area attached to a very comfy queen size bed and clean linen was very well welcomed after a 21+ hour flight.

bathroom is small but thats how bathrooms and showers in europe tend to be, so no big deal- perfect for what is meant to be used for. ;)

Now, apartment is located on the 3rd floor of the building, so expect to use the narrow stairs that this antique dutch houses were designed with. 

Host is almost never there, but he will def. be there to welcome you at one point during the day or night.  if you need anything shoot him a text message and he will reply back right away. Do not hesitate in asking him anything. 

Definitely will come back to Amsterdam and will definitely stay at Freek's apartment again.
